This paper proposes a deep learning solution for recognizing pedestrian traffic lights and zebra crossings for the visually impaired. The proposed solution is based on a convolutional neural network, which is a common approach in computer vision (cs.CV). The paper also focuses on the design of the network for accuracy and computational efficiency, which are important topics in machine learning (cs.LG). The use of deep learning for recognition tasks is also a common topic in artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The paper also mentions the importance of the solution for safe navigation, which is a topic in robotics (cs.RO). Finally, the paper discusses the potential impact of the solution for the visually impaired, which is a topic in human-computer interaction (cs.HC).
